<div style="color: #65CAFC; font-size: 24px;">Something is not working. What should I do?</div>

1) Refresh your browser (command R).<br>
2) If that doesn't work, clear your cache (command/shift/delete or "Clear Browsing Data" from the Chrome menu).<br>
3) Email bugs@zeega.org describing the issue as precisely as possible. We will get back to you within 24 hours.<br><br>

Soon there will be an awesome forum!<br><br>

<div style="color: #65CAFC; font-size: 24px;">How can I change the scale and opacity of media in a frame?</div>

When you drag media to the workspace, it automatically creates a layer under "Edit Layers." Click on this layer to see the layer-specific controls, which include sliders for scale and opacity.<br>

<img src="{{ asset('images/faq/edit-layer.jpg') }}" />

<div style="color: #65CAFC; font-size: 24px; ">How can I clip videos and audio?</div>

You can create clips from any audio or video in Zeega. Drag an audio or video item to the workspace, and then click on the layer under "Edit Layers." The item will load and then you can select the in/out points.<br>

<img src="{{ asset('images/faq/clip-video.jpg') }}" />

<div style="color: #65CAFC; font-size: 24px;">How exact can my audio/video edits be?</div>

For an .mp4 video or .mp3 audio file you can edit frame by frame. Open the audio or video layer control in the "Edit Layers" menu and double-click on the playhead, which will turn yellow. Then use the right/left arrow keys to adjust the in/out point. YouTube videos can only be excerpted up to 1/2 second.<br><br>

<div style="color: #65CAFC; font-size: 24px;">Can I create nonlinear links?</div>

Yes. Any layer can be linked to a unique URL. These URLs might be frames within a Zeega project (all frames have a unique URL you can copy when you view the link under "share") or any URL on the web. You can add this link by opening the specified layer in the "Edit Layers" menu and clicking on the "Link" icon at the bottom.<br><br>

<img src="{{ asset('images/faq/link-layer.jpg') }}" /><br><br>

